The textbook Birefringent Thin Films and Polarizing Elements by McCall, Hodgkinson, and Wu (2014) summarizes the Berreman calculus (Berreman, 1972; McCall, Hodgkinson, and Wu, 2014), which uses a 4×4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
