The system-model fits shown here to the March 2020 GOS lamp data set of Figure 8 show that we can reproduce 1872 NCSP measured fluxes to 0.5% photometric error levels using system models with 62 and 137 variables. A second on-Sun observing campaign also reproduced 1368 measured fluxes from 19 PolCals to similar 0.5% levels as in Figure 9. The metrology for mirror coatings and retarders gives a very close approximation of the system, with both sets of fitted values close to metrology expectations. We began with 17-variable model fits to the lamp-data set to show that the 24-variable modulation matrix matches the mirror and modulator metrology when restricting the modulation matrix to be a grouping of mirrors folded in the Q\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
