Different instruments sample the DKIST beam at a range of different field angles. Instruments all have opto-mechanical methods to select a particular field offset from the telescope bore sight either by using slit stepping or scanning mirrors mounted near pupil planes. The resultant field-angle dependence of the system Mueller-matrix elements was below ±0.02\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
