We use the FIDO BS-950 coating metrology on a 100 mm diameter stress sample at a wavelength of 1057 nm. See Harrington et al. (2021c, Section 2.3) for more details on this depolarization model. We propagate all possible input Stokes vectors through all locations across the optic aperture and then compute the depolarization as the aperture average. We find 1-DoP to be in a typical range of 1 to 10 parts per million. For particular wavelengths associated with narrow spectral features, the much more non-uniform coatings can cause 1-DoP to be at levels of parts per thousand. As expected for our simple model, there is only UV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
